comment.narrative:
1. There is no state run legal aid system and no Law on state guaranteed Legal Aid. The government Working Group developed a concept - vision on state run legal aid which is to be piloted after adoption (expected in September 2014); 
2. According to the evidence from development partners, in 2013 consultations were provided to 12,554 people, including 58% women and 13% persons with disabilities. 
3. Legal aid services delivered with the donor funding is mainly concentrated in Khatlon (6 offices), Soughd (8 offices) and GBAO  (4 offices) oblasts with limited presence in Rasht valley   (2 offices,  (8,8% of all consultations provided in 2013) 
4. 2011 UPR revealed 123 recommendations, including 22 gender and 6 recommendations specific to persons with disabilities;
5. In 2012, Tajikistan Ombudsman was accredited B status of compliance with Paris Principles;
6. According to the ‘UN Women Survey, 13% of households have a family member without registration document;
7. The Government Working Group on signing/ratification of the UN Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities was established in 2013;
8. There are no implementation mechanisms for the Law on prevention of violence in the family;

1. Concept-vision paper on the State guaranteed Legal Aid is adopted by the Government of Tajikistan;
2. At least 5,760 people, including 3,341 rural women and 749 persons with disabilities will be covered with state run Legal Aid Services;
3. At least 25,000 people are covered with legal awareness campaigns, including at least 50% rural women and 2% of persons with disabilities;
4. By the end of the project, UPR National Action Plan will be implemented by at least 40%;
5. Ombudsman’s compliance with Paris Principles will be strengthened;
6. By the end of the project, the number of households having a family member without a registration document reduced by at least 10% in two pilot districts;
7. The Action Plan (2014-2015) of the Government Working Group on ratification of the  UN Convention on the Rights of Persons is reviewed, strengthened and implemented by at least 70%;
8. Implementation mechanisms for the Law on Prevention of violence in the family are developed, introduced and functioning in at least 2 districts;

